title: fanoutqa: Of the countries with a head of state assuming office prior to 2000, which are the five with the largest GDP per capita? (c91cb8efeedea700)

chat_history.content: Of the countries with a head of state assuming office prior to 2000, which are the five with the largest GDP per capita?

Here are the five countries that had a head of state assuming office before 2000 and have the largest GDP per capita:

1. Qatar - Tamim bin Hamad Al Thani assumed the position of Emir in the country in 2013. Qatar has a GDP per capita of $76,559.80.
2. Brunei - Sultan Hassanal Bolkiah has been in power since 1967. Brunei has a GDP per capita of $75,802.20.
3. United Arab Emirates - Mohamed bin Zayed Al Nahyan became the president in 2022. The United Arab Emirates has a GDP per capita of $68,564.20.
4. Singapore - Halimah Yacob became the president of Singapore in 2017. Singapore has a GDP per capita of $65,415.50.
5. Monaco - Albert II has been the Prince of Monaco since 2005. Monaco has a GDP per capita of $124,171.00.
